import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    
    plt.boxplot([data['normal'], data['actual']], labels=['Normal', 'Actual'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of normal and actual temperatures?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.legend(['Normal', 'Actual'], loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]

    plt.plot(data['day'], data['forecast'], label='Forecast', color='blue')
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['actual'], label='Actual', color='red')
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.title('How does the forecasted temperature compare to the actual temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecast'].plot.hist(bins=20, alpha=0.5, color='blue', label='Forecasted Temperatures')
    plt.axvline(data['forecast'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['forecast'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of forecasted temperatures?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Forecasted Temperatures")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
